its which sell their stock in a single day they raise money over time sometimes taking several years before closing an offeringcounting on high demandinland residential plans to buy class a and class b multifamily properties in the top  us metropolitan areas according to a filing with the securities and exchange commission like many apartment investors inland residential is counting on strong demand for apartments from baby boomers and millennials“demographic studies suggest that baby boomers are downsizing their suburban homes and relocating to multifamily units located in urban cultural centers” the company said in the filing “millennials are renting multifamily units because they generally have a high level of student debt and credit standards for mortgage loans have increased both of which hinder millennials from buying traditional singlefamily detached houses”inland group declined to comment citing federal law that limits what companies can say ahead of stock offeringsinland group was the top fundraiser in the nontraded reit industry during the boom its reits and other inland investment vehicles raked in more than  billion in the year period ended june  according to the filingyet the company fell off its perch after the crash amid increased competition and struggles at two of its reits retail properties of america inc and inland american real estate trust inc its sixth reit inland real estate income trust launched about two years ago had raised just  million through sept  according to the sec filing a small amount compared with other nontraded reits the classes of multifamily properties inland residential plans to buy has been corrected inland american real estate trust inc inland group inc retail properties of america inc ipos residential real estate apartments reits chicago real estate daily get our exclusive news about the chicagoarea commercial real estate industry read next ambassador an old chicago hotel name is new again investors in loop apartment building make peace cut deal medical office building planned for lincoln park bowling anyone office workers may soon have their chance